keyValuePair.Value: Were you disappointed your team couldn't find a winner in the second half?
The first half was pretty tight today but I guess you still thought you'd go on to win the game. Are you disappointed your boys couldn't find a second-half winner?
The lads know they can be better than that.

I was surprised we didn't make more chances after the break. We dominated for most of the second half. One goal and I think we'd have gone on to win. The lads know they're capable of better, but perhaps today just wasn't their day.

I'm pleased enough with the draw.

In the first half, it looked like the game could go either way. We were up against a decent team. In the second half, we did most of the pressing but %1s could have been dangerous on the break. Overall, I'm not so disappointed with the draw.

If we could have got to half time ahead, I think we'd have won. So I'm disappointed we conceded when we did. The boys have to be more determined. We have to be more difficult to get through. I'm very disappointed we didn't come out on top today.

I want to see us attack with more energy.

We wanted to keep it solid and we did that. Then, you're looking for one moment of magic from someone, to create the chance that can decide the game. Unfortunately we couldn't find a winner today. But the lads will move on from this, I'm sure.
We were really determined out there.

If you can keep a clean sheet, you always have a chance. We couldn't find a winner but, out of possession, I thought the team was outstanding today. In the end, we had to grind it out. Credit to the boys for doing that and making sure we came away with a draw.
We were never at our best today

Defensively we were pretty good today but never got enough players forward to create the chance that could have decided the game. With a clean sheet, it's always there to be won. But the lads didn't ever impose themselves. I never felt we were 100% in control out there. We've missed an opportunity, for sure.

We were convinced we could win the game today but things didn't go our way. So credit to the lads for keeping going and making sure we didn't lose. There were chances at both ends. I'm just sorry we didn't take one of ours.

We were convinced we could win the game today but things didn't go our way. So credit to the lads for keeping going and making sure we didn't lose. There were chances at both ends. I'm just sorry we didn't take one of ours.
Were you worried when they got the equaliser?
The game was there to be won but, after conceding the equaliser, were you worried your team might drop off and end up losing?
Maybe we thought we'd already done enough to win.

We had the lead and maybe we thought the game was already won. But you can't ever relax and, after we conceded the equaliser, we couldn't pick the momentum up. Switch off and you can't just switch on again. It's a lesson this team has to learn.
I'm happy we didn't lose, to be honest!
I expected us to go on and win the game but, after they equalised, the momentum shifted and we had to work hard to make sure we didn't lose. A draw was probably the right result in the end.

I thought we'd done enough to win. We looked pretty comfortable. But we got pulled out of our shape just for a moment and that cost us the equaliser. We have to be more focused. Giving that goal away meant the balance shifted and, in the end, we were probably happy to scrape a draw.

Did you think you'd go on and win the game today?
Once you'd drawn level, the momentum seemed to be with your team. But you couldn't build on that. Why do you think your team wasn't able to find a second-half winner?
We should have gone on and found a winner.
We should have gone on and found a winner.

We had 45 minutes to find a winner but we came up short and had to settle for the draw. Look, the boys worked hard enough but I expected a little more quality from them in the final third. They know they can do better than they did today.

We've conceded a really poor goal.

Was that a game you could have lost today?
It didn't look good at half-time. You were behind and looked second-best. How pleased were you with the way the team responded and got back into the game after the break?
We were resilient today.
We were resilient today.

I think we finally managed to impose ourselves on the game in the second half. We were first to the loose balls and created chances. We didn't let our heads drop. We got the equaliser we deserved and maybe we were unlucky not to win in the end.

We started slowly and just couldn't get into the game early on, and we paid the price for that. We were under a lot of pressure. The second half was better but, even so, I think we expected better than a draw today. I just wanted to see a bit of inspiration from someone to turn things our way.

I was worried at half-time. We didn't play well early on and we conceded a bad goal. So I give the boys credit for turning things round second half. We got back into it and could maybe even have gone on and won the game.

Were you grateful to scrape a draw at the end?
Going into the last few minutes, your team looked beaten. But that late goal saved you. Was that draw deserved or a bit of a lucky break?
I like a team that never gives up!

If you've got players who are willing to run and chase for the whole of the 90 minutes, you've always got a chance. We were determined to get something out of the game. The goal came late but I thought the boys deserved it for all their hard work.
We need to start games better.

We were pushing and pushing for the equaliser. I thought the boys did well to keep the pressure on the opposition. We never let them out second half. But we need to start games with that kind of intensity in future. That's how we'll turn draws like this one into wins.
Not one player lost his head.

Even though we were under pressure for long periods and conceded a poor goal, I thought the lads did well to keep their heads. We didn't panic. We made sure we stayed solid defensively and, from there, we found the impetus we needed to go on and rescue a draw.

You must have thought the game was won. What happened?

It looked like you were going to see the game out for a win but %1s found the equaliser right at the end. It must be frustrating to have to settle for the draw. Are you disappointed your boys couldn't hang on?
One defensive error can be expensive.
Yes, I expected a win today.

It drives me crazy! We played very well and definitely deserved to win. Defensively, I thought we always seemed to have good control of the game. But it's never over till it's over. One lapse in concentration and we've thrown it away. The boys have to learn to keep going for the whole 90-plus minutes.
Yes, winning was the expectation today. I would have liked to see us push forward more after pulling level, and go for the win.
We have to take it on the chin.

I thought we played really well for most of the game and deserved to win. But a one-goal margin is never enough and we paid the price. We'll just have to take the positives and make sure we close games out in the future.
I'm very disappointed we weren't able to go on and win after pulling level. As far as I'm concerned, we should be aiming for a win in every match.
You need to get your goals when you're on top.

We were much the better side for most of the game. When you're so dominant, though, you need to press home the advantage and put the game out of reach. Instead, we eased up. Us being only a goal in front meant they were always in it. Them getting that late equaliser was a real body blow.
